{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:04:36.622Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Weight Decay — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Weight Decay Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a regularization technique that adds a small penalty—usually the L2 norm of all weights—to the loss function to prevent overfitting. It acts as a regularizer that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "penalizes large weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in the network, encouraging the model to learn smaller weights that capture underlying patterns rather than memorizing training data."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Often called "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", weight decay is a fundamental technique used to improve model performance across everything from image classification to large language models."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Weight Decay Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay provides several critical benefits:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalizes memorization of training data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All generative models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stabilizes training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents weights from growing too large"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diffusion models, VAEs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improves generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better performance on unseen data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LLMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents exploding gradients"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keeps weights bounded"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large-scale models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Promotes feature sharing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encourages similar weights across neurons"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complex architectures"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "broadly used"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for training state-of-the-art deep networks, but its role in modern deep learning is different from classical learning theory—it changes training dynamics rather than acting as explicit regularization."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Weight Decay Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Penalty Term"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay adds a penalty term proportional to the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "sum of squared weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{loss} = \\text{original\\_loss} + \\frac{\\lambda}{2} \\times \\sum w^{2}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\lambda"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay parameter (e.g., "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "10^{-4}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " or 0.01)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "w"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All weights in the model"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two Implementation Methods"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adds penalty term to loss function"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay in optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modifies update rule to include decay factor"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update Rule"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay modifies the optimizer's update rule to reduce weights at each step:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Plain gradient descent with weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nw"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{t+1} = w_t - \\text{lr} \\times \\text{grad} - \\text{lr} \\times \\lambda \\times w_t\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This subtracts a fraction of the weights directly during the update step."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay vs. L2 Regularization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Historically, they were treated as the same thing, but they're "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "mathematically different"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in adaptive optimizers:"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "L2 Regularization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Added to the loss function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\n\\text{loss} = \\text{original\\"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "loss} + \\frac{\\lambda}{2} \\times \\sum w^2\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient becomes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\n\\text{grad} = \\text{original\\"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "grad} + \\lambda \\times w\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay (Decoupled)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applied directly to parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nw"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{t+1} = w_t - \\text{lr} \\times \\text{grad} - \\text{lr} \\times \\lambda \\times w_t\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay subtracts from the parameter itself, not from the gradient."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay in Optimizers"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Adam (L2 Regularization)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Adam applies weight decay by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "adding it to the gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Adam's \"weight decay\" (L2 regularization)\ngrad = grad.add(param, alpha=weight_decay)  # Adds to gradient [web:156]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem: The regularization term appears in both numerator and denominator of Adam's adaptive learning rate, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "minimizing its effect"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In AdamW (Decoupled Weight Decay)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AdamW "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "decouples weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from the adaptive gradient update, applying it directly to parameters:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# AdamW's weight decay (decoupled)\nparam.mul_(1 - lr * weight_decay)  # Subtracts from parameter [web:156]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This subtracts a fraction of weights directly during the update step."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using Weight Decay Parameter"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.optim as optim\n\nmodel = torch.nn.Linear(10, 1)\n\n# SGD with weight decay (1e-4 is default)\noptimizer_sgd = optim.SGD(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=1e-3,\n    weight_decay=1e-4  # L2 regularization parameter [web:165]\n)\n\n# Adam with weight decay (not recommended for LLMs)\noptimizer_adam = optim.Adam(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=1e-3,\n    weight_decay=1e-4  # L2 regularization (interferes with adaptive LR) [web:156]\n)\n\n# AdamW with weight decay (recommended default)\noptimizer_adamw = optim.AdamW(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=1e-3,\n    weight_decay=0.01  # Proper decoupled weight decay [web:156]\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Default Values"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Weight Decay"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1e-4 (0.0001)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1e-4 (0.0001)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.01 (default)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight Decay in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n# Adam with L2 regularization (not decoupled)\noptimizer_adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(\n    learning_rate=0.001,\n    weight_decay=None  # L2 regularization not recommended [web:156]\n)\n\n# AdamW with decoupled weight decay (recommended)\noptimizer_adamw = tf.keras.optimizers.AdamW(\n    learning_rate=0.001,\n    weight_decay=0.004  # Default weight decay [web:156]\n)\n\n# Training\nmodel.fit(\n    train_data,\n    train_labels,\n    epochs=100,\n    optimizer=optimizer_adamw\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Weight Decay"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Weight Decay When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting is a concern"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model memorizes training data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training large models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": LLMs, diffusion models, transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using AdamW"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard practice with default 0.01"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improving generalization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Need better test performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Don't Use Weight Decay When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using BatchNorm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Can interfere with normalization layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate is very high"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": May cause instability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple tasks"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Overfitting unlikely"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tuning Weight Decay"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The optimal value depends on:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Larger models → more weight decay needed\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Less data → more weight decay needed\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Higher LR → may need less weight decay\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Task complexity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Complex tasks → balance regularization vs. performance"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Values"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1e-6 to 1e-4"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small models, plenty of data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1e-4 to 1e-3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard deep learning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "0.01 to 0.1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LLMs (AdamW default)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "0.1 to 1.0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very large models, scarce data"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Finding Best Value"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "grid search"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "hyperparameter optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cross-validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to find the best weight decay parameter."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern Perspective on Weight Decay"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classical vs. Modern View"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classical learning theory"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay acts as explicit regularizer to prevent overfitting."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Modern deep learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "changes training dynamics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in desirable ways:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vision tasks (multipass SGD)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enhances implicit regularization of SGD via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loss stabilization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LLMs (one-epoch training)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Balances "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "bias-variance tradeoff"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in stochastic optimization, leading to lower training loss"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight decay is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "never useful as an explicit regularizer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " but instead modifies optimization dynamics attractively."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rotational Equilibrium"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay can create "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "equilibrium states"}, {"type": "text", "text": " where gradient updates and weight decay cancel out on average:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Effective learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " becomes constant across layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Eliminates chaotic transient phase"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simplifies training dynamics"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This rotational equilibrium may explain why "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW outperforms Adam with L2 regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of weight decay as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "a gentle tug toward zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient pushes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning direction based on data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay pulls"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Softly pulls weights toward zero"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weights stay small but not zero"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Balance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model learns patterns without memorizing"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine a ball rolling down a hill:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ball rolls downhill (toward minimum loss)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Friction pulls ball slightly back toward origin\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Equilibrium"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ball settles at minimum but not too far"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Regularization by adding L2 norm of weights to loss function"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Penalizes large weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Encourages smaller weights that capture patterns, not memorization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better generalization on unseen data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stabilizes training"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevents exploding gradients by bounding weights"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Update formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "w_{t+1} = w_t - \\text{lr} \\times \\text{grad} - \\text{lr} \\times \\lambda \\times w_t"}}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "L2 regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adds to loss function (then gradient)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weight decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Applied directly to parameters (decoupled)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam's bug"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": L2 regularization interferes with adaptive learning rate"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW's fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Decoupled weight decay applied directly to parameters"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Typical values"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 1e-4 (standard), 0.01 (AdamW default)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard weight decay is 0.01"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Modern view"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Changes training dynamics, not explicit regularizer"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vision tasks"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enhances implicit regularization via loss stabilization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LLMs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Balances bias-variance tradeoff, improves training stability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rotational equilibrium"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Can balance effective learning rate across layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weight decay is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "powerful and widely used technique"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that significantly improves model performance by preventing overfitting, promoting feature sharing, and improving model stability—essential for building robust, generalizable deep learning models."}]}]}}